items.title: So this is a long story. And I don't usually like things like this or try to call attention to myself and that's definitely not what this is. I just think it's important for people to know what others go through so maybe they can also get help. Almost exactly a year ago this week, the middle of March 2013, I made plans to kill myself, and was very close to going through with them. My life pretty much crumbled around me last year, with too many stresses and things that hurt me. The whole months of March and April last year were a painful blur, and I don't know how I got though every day. All I know is that it was incredibly hard. As a person who's had a lot of issues with depression and plus all the other things going on, it all just seemed too much to handle and I was ready to end it. I can remember driving home from work one day, thinking how much better it would be if I just crashed and died. At that point, I had almost given up, and the one thing, silly as it was, that kept me going was the fact that the new Fall Out Boy album hadn't come out yet. On my worst days I just kept telling myself that I couldn't leave the earth till I heard that album. So I think I can say that that band practically saved my life. It has taken me almost a year later, being here at MSU to feel better and go back to being myself. Anti-depressants and therapy have helped me so much, and I encourage anyone who thinks they need that to look into getting that kind of help. I still consider myself a depressed person, but I am one who is doing so much better and it scares me to death to think I almost didn't give myself the chance for things to improve. It gets better. Find something to hold onto if you feel like that, even the cd you know you don't want to die without hearing ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è
